- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the design of a distributed observer for a linear system. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is also likely as the observer is designed for multiple agents to estimate the state of the system. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the observer is distributed among multiple agents. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses results from decentralized control theory. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is unlikely as there is no mention of neural networks or evolutionary algorithms in the abstract.
